description: Fringe of an early Roman settlement that appears to have expanded to renew an area of early and middle Iron Age settlement. The settlement included a 2nd - 3rd CE masonry circular building foundation, which was interpreted as a shrine with little evidence to support that.
bibliography: Leech. “Land off Coxwell Road, Faringdon,” 2010. https://doi.org/10.5284/1009202.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Coxwell Road, Faringdon (Oxfordshire).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
